The Lake Region Economic Bloc has contracted Deloitte East Africa to advise it on the planned establishment of a Sh2.8 billion regional bank. The financial institution will be unveiled in October. It is one of the flagship projects under the financial services pillar as envisaged in the blocâ€™s economic blueprint. Member counties are Kisumu, Homa Bay, Kakamega, Vihiga, Busia, Siaya, Bungoma, Migori, Bomet, Nandi, Kericho, Trans Nzoia, Kisii and Nyamira. Residents will be able to access loans for investment. Bloc chairman Wycliffe Oparanya (Kakamega) yesterday said Sh700 million has been contributed.